  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: If I click on a transaction that I've sent, the Transaction Details screen shows initial state of the transaction. It's not getting refreshed but I assume it should be. The only way to refresh it is by going to Transaction History and opening the transaction there.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/41653495-8e6ba850-7486-11e8-81db-c2b3a181adb2.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/41653843-a0ce6874-7487-11e8-9c7b-7c6899ea33e2.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nWhen transaction message in chat is clicked, the transaction details shows most up to date info.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nThe transaction details shows old state of transaction.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status on 2 devices\r\n- Create 1-1 chat beteen devices\r\n- Device A: send tokens (\"/send\") to device B\r\n- Wait for some time until transaction is confirmed or at least has some confirmations\r\n- Device A: click on the transaction message\r\n-> Device A: Transaction Details shows but data is not up to date.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.20\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n",
